(SCREAMING)

784
01:04:34,937 --> 01:04:36,234
Please.

785
01:04:36,305 --> 01:04:38,205
Please, don't tease him.
Please.

786
01:04:38,340 --> 01:04:40,274
Please,
just stop hurting him.

787
01:04:40,342 --> 01:04:41,934
Please!

788
01:04:43,812 --> 01:04:46,679
This is the police!
Put the gun down now!

789
01:04:50,018 --> 01:04:51,144
No.

790
01:04:51,220 --> 01:04:52,915
You useless waste!

791
01:04:52,988 --> 01:04:54,649
No! No!

792
01:04:54,723 --> 01:04:56,213
(SCREAMING)

793
01:04:58,193 --> 01:04:59,717
No!

794
01:05:03,265 --> 01:05:04,254
GRACE: (SOBBING) No!

795
01:05:04,767 --> 01:05:06,860
Get your hands off of me!

796
01:05:08,937 --> 01:05:10,768
<i>OFFICER: Get up here!
Get up here!</i>

797
01:05:10,839 --> 01:05:13,069
<i>Let's go, man. This way!</i>

798
01:05:13,275 --> 01:05:14,435
<i>(SIRENS WAILING)</i>

799
01:05:14,643 --> 01:05:17,510
<i>(GRACE SCREAMING)</i>

800
01:05:21,583 --> 01:05:23,881
<i>JOHN: I want to die.</i>

801
01:05:26,789 --> 01:05:28,848
<i>(JIM SCREAMING)</i>

802
01:05:29,725 --> 01:05:32,193
<i>- GRACE: No!
- Grace?</i>

803
01:05:42,371 --> 01:05:44,771
Grace, do you know
who this man is?

804
01:05:48,444 --> 01:05:50,344
That's the real John Ryder.

805
01:05:50,479 --> 01:05:52,379
He's been missing
since Tuesday.

806
01:05:58,020 --> 01:05:59,180
Then who...

807
01:05:59,254 --> 01:06:00,380
We don't know yet.

808
01:06:00,989 --> 01:06:02,650
Now, we've run
his fingerprints
and mug shots

809
01:06:02,724 --> 01:06:03,782
through every database
we've got,

810
01:06:03,859 --> 01:06:04,917
and we've come up
with nothing.

811
01:06:04,993 --> 01:06:06,858
This guy's a ghost.

812
01:06:06,962 --> 01:06:09,931
<i>So, I need your help
here, Grace.</i>

813
01:06:10,032 --> 01:06:12,796
<i>Is there anything
he told you about himself?</i>

814
01:06:13,402 --> 01:06:14,528
<i>No.</i>

815
01:06:15,471 --> 01:06:16,563
<i>Anything at all?</i>

816
01:06:20,709 --> 01:06:21,733
No.

817
01:06:28,617 --> 01:06:30,175
Open cell F!

818
01:06:32,921 --> 01:06:37,415
Ryder, I need you to stand up
and put your hands
behind your back.

819
01:06:37,493 --> 01:06:40,860
I need you to stand up,
put your hands
behind your back.

820
01:06:57,779 --> 01:06:59,041
(CLEARS THROAT)

821
01:07:01,483 --> 01:07:03,144
So, where are you from?

822
01:07:04,253 --> 01:07:05,515
All over.

823
01:07:07,723 --> 01:07:09,020
Is that so?

824
01:07:11,460 --> 01:07:13,655
You're a sick fuck,
aren't ya?

825
01:07:14,563 --> 01:07:17,054
The way you tortured
that young man.

826
01:07:17,499 --> 01:07:19,490
I know
you enjoyed yourself.

827
01:07:21,603 --> 01:07:23,264
I just can't figure out
why you did it.

828
01:07:23,405 --> 01:07:25,100
You knew
you'd get caught.

829
01:07:25,173 --> 01:07:26,765
Why'd you do it?

830
01:07:28,544 --> 01:07:29,772
Why not?

831
01:07:33,081 --> 01:07:35,481
How many others
have you killed?

832
01:07:40,155 --> 01:07:41,554
Hard to say.

833
01:07:45,794 --> 01:07:48,024
You see,
here in the great state
of New Mexico,

834
01:07:48,163 --> 01:07:50,393
we do have
the death penalty.

835
01:07:52,868 --> 01:07:54,961
You don't seem
too worried.

836
01:07:58,073 --> 01:07:59,472
Should I be?

837
01:08:04,546 --> 01:08:06,946
You comfy down there, John?

838
01:08:07,382 --> 01:08:09,509
Are those cuffs
a little tight?

839
01:08:10,285 --> 01:08:11,912
Yeah, a little tight.

840
01:08:11,987 --> 01:08:14,717
Yeah, you see,
those are the new ones.

841
01:08:17,559 --> 01:08:20,926
They stretch out after
you wear them for a while.
Let me see.

842
01:08:23,031 --> 01:08:24,020
(EXCLAIMS IN PAIN)

843
01:08:24,666 --> 01:08:26,190
Look at me.

844
01:08:29,938 --> 01:08:32,133
You have yourself
a nice trip.

845
01:08:33,342 --> 01:08:35,435
We'll chat again real soon.

846
01:08:36,511 --> 01:08:39,309
Maybe next time,
you'll be better company.

847
01:09:13,582 --> 01:09:14,571
Thanks.

848
01:09:18,020 --> 01:09:19,749
Where are we going?

849
01:09:20,155 --> 01:09:23,318
I'm taking you to Albuquerque
for trauma support.

850
01:09:23,525 --> 01:09:25,925
I can release you
to your parents there.

851
01:09:52,621 --> 01:09:53,986
OFFICER: Step up.

852
01:10:42,938 --> 01:10:45,099
03 X-ray,
we're about 20 minutes out.

853
01:10:45,173 --> 01:10:46,936
<i>DISPATCHER:
Copy that, 03 X-ray.</i>

854
01:10:50,212 --> 01:10:51,406
OFFICER: I get home,
I look at my paycheck.

855
01:10:51,480 --> 01:10:52,469
It's so skinny.

856
01:10:53,248 --> 01:10:54,738
I decide to take
another job.

857
01:10:54,883 --> 01:10:56,407
So now
I'm delivering pizza.

858
01:11:04,326 --> 01:11:06,419
What are you
getting your daughter
for her birthday?

859
01:11:06,528 --> 01:11:08,655
She's just turned five.

860
01:11:08,730 --> 01:11:10,254
She wants to take me...
Go to the mall,

861
01:11:10,332 --> 01:11:12,266
get one of those big
customized teddy bears.

862
01:11:12,334 --> 01:11:13,858
A customized teddy bear?
Come on.

863
01:11:13,935 --> 01:11:15,266
Yeah.

864
01:11:15,337 --> 01:11:18,135
It's just another way
they can charge...

865
01:11:39,594 --> 01:11:41,255
ESTERIDGE: Look, Grace...

866
01:11:42,998 --> 01:11:44,124
I wish I could have
stopped this

867
01:11:44,199 --> 01:11:47,066
before it got
all out of control.

868
01:11:49,004 --> 01:11:52,838
I know there's
nothing that I can say
that'll bring Jim back,

869
01:11:54,876 --> 01:11:56,434
but I am sorry.

870
01:11:57,612 --> 01:11:59,045
I truly am.

871
01:12:01,983 --> 01:12:04,315
Get your own little pants,
your own little jacket.

872
01:12:04,386 --> 01:12:06,411
Make your own
little teddy bear.

873
01:12:23,839 --> 01:12:25,670
For real, you spent
100 bucks on a teddy bear?

874
01:12:25,740 --> 01:12:27,230
Yeah, I know.
It was hurting me.

875
01:12:27,375 --> 01:12:28,865
Yeah, it's 100 bucks...

876
01:12:31,780 --> 01:12:34,214
You know,
this week's check,
it's gone.

877
01:12:54,836 --> 01:12:56,565
Stop moving.

878
01:12:56,638 --> 01:12:58,230
What the fuck?

879
01:13:06,348 --> 01:13:07,337
It's cool...

880
01:13:10,252 --> 01:13:11,344
Oh, shit!

881
01:13:16,591 --> 01:13:18,218
Son of a bitch!

882
01:13:35,911 --> 01:13:37,208
(GROANING)

883
01:13:37,279 --> 01:13:38,906
My leg's stuck.

884
01:13:44,753 --> 01:13:46,277
03 X-ray.

885
01:13:46,354 --> 01:13:48,845
I need a Code 3 backup
on Highway 19.

886
01:13:49,124 --> 01:13:50,648
<i>DISPATCHER: 10-4, 03 X-ray.</i>

887
01:13:50,992 --> 01:13:55,122
Grace, I want you
to run up over that hill
and wait there for help.

888
01:13:56,331 --> 01:13:58,231
I'm done running.

889
01:13:58,300 --> 01:14:00,632
Grace! Grace!

890
01:14:01,736 --> 01:14:03,601
That's not the answer.

891
01:14:04,005 --> 01:14:05,700
You don't know
what you're doing.

892
01:14:05,774 --> 01:14:07,105
Yes, I do.

893
01:14:14,816 --> 01:14:15,976
Grace!

894
01:14:24,259 --> 01:14:26,022
ESTERIDGE: Grace, be careful!

895
01:14:32,734 --> 01:14:33,723
(EXCLAIMS)

896
01:14:41,209 --> 01:14:42,733
Backup, now!
Let's go!

897
01:14:48,483 --> 01:14:51,543
03 X-ray. Where the hell
is my goddamn backup?

898
01:14:56,191 --> 01:14:57,954
You better hurry.

899
01:15:02,630 --> 01:15:04,097
(BANGING ON DOOR)

900
01:15:33,261 --> 01:15:34,250
(GRUNTING)

901
01:15:54,916 --> 01:15:56,213
Grace!

902
01:16:19,607 --> 01:16:21,234
Go fuck yourself!

903
01:16:25,313 --> 01:16:26,337
No!

904
01:17:05,053 --> 01:17:06,350
(RIFLE COCKING)

905
01:17:33,648 --> 01:17:35,673
Feels good, doesn't it?

906
01:17:37,152 --> 01:17:39,017
I don't feel a thing.

